"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:11.3.1.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">11.3.1.3</span> Ephah</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אֵיפָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(’eyfah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:36\">EXO 16:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:11\">LEV 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:13\">LEV 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:36\">LEV 19:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:15\">NUM 5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:5\">NUM 28:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:14\">DEU 25:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:14\">DEU 25:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:15\">DEU 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:19\">JDG 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:17\">RUT 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:24\">1SA 1:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:17\">1SA 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:10\">ISA 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:10\">EZK 45:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:11\">EZK 45:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:11\">EZK 45:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:13\">EZK 45:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:13\">EZK 45:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:24\">EZK 45:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:24\">EZK 45:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:24\">EZK 45:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:5\">EZK 46:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:5\">EZK 46:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:7\">EZK 46:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:7\">EZK 46:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:7\">EZK 46:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:11\">EZK 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:11\">EZK 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:11\">EZK 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:14\">EZK 46:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:10\">MIC 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:6\">ZEC 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:7\">ZEC 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:8\">ZEC 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:9\">ZEC 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:10\">ZEC 5:10</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">The <em>’eyfah</em> is the dry equivalent to the <em>bath</em> liquid measure.</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In six of the above passages (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:36\">EXO 16:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:11\">LEV 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:21\">LEV 14:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:15\">NUM 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:4\">NUM 15:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:5\">NUM 28:5</a>), the quantity mentioned is 1/10 of an <em>’eyfah</em>, which equals an <em>‘omer</em> (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:36\">EXO 16:36</a>). In these passages it will be possible to use the same word that has been chosen to render <em>‘omer</em>.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:36\">LEV 19:36</a>: This command to have just measures may need to be adjusted in some languages. It is not the absolute value of the <em>’eyfah</em> or the <em>hin</em> which should be just, but rather the accurate capacity of the containers that are supposed to measure them. A merchant should not be doing business with a container that is supposed to contain an <em>’eyfah</em> but which actually holds less. It is possible to expand this to include enough extra information to give the reader understanding. Thus for the literal phrase “a just ephah, and a just hin” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>), <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> has “with your weighing baskets the right size and your jars holding the right amount of liquid.” This, however, may be too cumbersome. Perhaps best is <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> with “don’t cheat when you … measure anything.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
